                <p>Thanks to the energies and efforts of Society mem- ber Dottie DeBisschop the Oxford Historical Society applied for and received funding provided by the Connecti- cut State Department of Economic and Community De- velopment/Connecticut Office of the Arts (COA) from the Connecticut State Legislature. An additional grant was provided from the CT Humanities (CTH) through the Sustaining the Humanities through the American Rescue Plan with monies from the National Endowment for the Humanities (NEH) and the federal American Res- cue Plan (ARP) Act.</p>
